(219, 2, '2011-10-11 11:36:03', '2011-10-11 11:36:03', 'Rabies is a viral infection usually spread by the saliva of infected animals. Human cases are usually due to dog bites but many animals can be infected, and a scratch or lick may be sufficient to transmite the disease. Rabies is fatal once symptoms begin.', 'Rabies', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rabies', '', '', '2011-10-13 13:44:19', '2011-10-13 13:44:19', '', 0, 'http://dlvs-uk.konscript.com/?post_type=vaccination&#038;p=219', 0, 'vaccination', '', 0),
(1134, 2, '2012-01-12 12:27:10', '2012-01-12 12:27:10', 'The rules and coverage areas and travel insurance can vary from company to company. It is important to be properly covered, or you''ll risk being met with extraordinary large claims for payment of a received treatment abroad.\r\n\r\nThe Yellow Card provides coverage for illness in the short tourist trips within Europe. Health insurance card does not cover hjemtransport.Det is also important to examine coverage for lost holidays, canceled vacations, lost baggage and possible accidents. Be aware that certain sports (eg. Diving, skiing, climbing, paragliding) can be excluded coverage at all.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - travel insurance:\r\n\r\n* Always have an adequate travel insurance.\r\n* Check if your travel provider has a special arrangement with an insurance company.\r\n* Check if your regular insurance company has an annual travel insurance.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Yellow Card\r\n\r\n* You are covered by your yellow health card in another country, you\r\n* Travels in less than a month.\r\n* Is on a holiday or study tour.\r\n* Travel within the EU and EEA as well as some small states.\r\n* Not have a chronic illness such as hypertension.\r\n\r\n\r\nRecovery of costs\r\n\r\n* The Yellow Card ensures that you receive reimbursement of your expenses, equal to the domestic coverage.\r\n* You may risk having to pay for medical care and medications directly at the resort.\r\n* Remember to get receipts for your expenses.\r\n* You can recover your expenses by contacting the SOS International. You should always file a claim form. You can report damage online at the SOS website.\r\n* If in doubt abroad you can use the phone number printed on the back of the card and get guidance from the telephone-call service, which is open around the clock.\r\n\r\n\r\nEU Blue card\r\n\r\nYou must have a European blue card on travel to an EU / EEA country when you:\r\n\r\n* Must be gone longer than 30 days.\r\n* Do an internship or an au pair.\r\n* Study or receive vocational training.\r\n* If you have a chronic illness.\r\n* If you must work your Danish employers abroad, you must have an approved E101 from the Social Security Agency, to get the Blue card.\r\n* The blue EU Health Insurance Card is free. You can order it from your municipality''s citizen service.', 'Insurance', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1089-revision-3', '', '', '2012-01-12 12:27:10', '2012-01-12 12:27:10', '', 1089, 'http://dlvs-uk.konscript.net/1089-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
