(1072, 2, '2012-01-12 10:18:38', '2012-01-12 10:18:38', 'All food is a potential source of infection. Be careful when choosing what you eat. This will reduce the risk of tourist diarrhea and more serious infections such as. infectious hepatitis, cholera, typhoid and dysentery.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - food:\r\n\r\n* Always keep a good hand hygiene.\r\n* Avoid putting fingers in their mouths.\r\n* Cook food itself if possible.\r\n* Stick to the safe food and stay away from the unsafe food:\r\n\r\nSAFE FOODS\r\n\r\n* Freshly boiled rice.\r\n* Freshly cooked pasta.\r\n* Scalding hot coffee and tea.\r\n* Bread.\r\n* Although tampering / peeled fruit.\r\n* Freshly boiled / nystegt food.\r\n* Bottled water.\r\n* Drinking from the bottle as you open\r\n\r\nUnsafe food\r\n\r\n* Ice cream and ice cubes.\r\n* Salads.\r\n* Uncooked vegetables.\r\n* Raw fish or raw meat.\r\n* Buffetmad\r\n* Unpasteurized milk products.\r\n* Water from the tap.\r\n* Fruits you have not tampered or garbage.\r\n* Dressing containing raw eggs such. mayonnaise.', 'Food', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'food', '', '', '2012-06-18 10:20:38', '2012-06-18 10:20:38', '', 413, 'http://dlvs-uk.konscript.net/?page_id=1072', 0, 'page', '', 0),
