(1056, 2, '2012-01-12 10:07:38', '2012-01-12 10:07:38', 'Colds caused by infection with flu virus and is not uncommon for travel. There are over 200 different viruses can cause colds. Colds typically contagious from the day before the disease breaks out for 1-3 days after disease outbreak. You typically infected through airborne droplets generated by coughing, sneezing, saliva or if, for example. via a handle, it has acquired infection on your hands, and then leads a hand up to eyes or nose.\r\n\r\nGenerally, the risk of colds 4 times as great in winter as in summer. There may be several reasons for colds in connection with travel.\r\n\r\nFor flights you will find yourself often for many hours with several hundred people in very little space. The more co-passengers there are and the longer the journey the greater the risk of becoming infected.\r\n\r\nMany indicate that air conditioning provides a cold, it is not clear whether this is the case. However, we know that air conditioning dries out the nasal membranes. Dry membranes are more vulnerable to infections. Moreover multiply cold virus better if you have cold air in the nose.\r\n\r\nWhen traveling to foreign places, there is also a greater risk that you are exposed to cold viruses as you have less resistance to the virus than you are exposed to at home.\r\n\r\nOutbreaks of cold sores caused by herpes simplex virus and it can be annoying when traveling.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - the prevention of colds:\r\n\r\n* It can be difficult to prevent colds, as the disease is transmitted from the day before you become ill, but the team as far as possible away to people who appear cold.\r\n* Wash hands frequently and avoid bringing them up to the face.\r\n* Ensure good ventilation if possible.\r\n* If one of your fellow travelers will be cold, it is important that he / she is instructed in good hand hygiene.\r\n* Turn down the air conditioning at night.\r\n* Slept like with decent cover in the form of blanket or similar.\r\n\r\n\r\nTravel advice - the relief of colds:\r\n\r\n* Nasal congestion can be alleviated by the use of nose drops or spray, available over the counter.\r\n* Pain in the neck can be relieved with lozenges ..\r\n* Many people find it soothing to hold your head over a basin with hot water and inhale the steam.\r\n* Sleeping with head elevated at night. For colds in children, you may want to lift the headboard of the bed, or use multiple pillows.\r\n\r\n\r\nTravel advice - colds and antibiotics:\r\n\r\n* Colds caused by viruses, and antibiotics such as penicillin has no effect on the disease. Only in case of complications, for example. in the form of sinusitis or otitis media, you should seek medical advice in order to evaluate whether there should be given antibiotics.\r\n\r\n\r\nTravel advice - cold sores:\r\n\r\n* By protecting your lips from sun and wind with a lip balm with sunscreen reduces the risk of getting cold sores.\r\n* Do you get a cold sore should wounded protected with lip balm with SPF.\r\n* At the first signs of outbreak (swollen and tingling around the lips area), started treatment with ointment against herpes virus', 'Colds', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'colds', '', '', '2012-06-18 10:20:38', '2012-06-18 10:20:38', '', 413, 'http://dlvs-uk.konscript.net/?page_id=1056', 0, 'page', '', 0),
