(1059, 2, '2012-01-12 10:09:26', '2012-01-12 10:09:26', 'Anyone can suffer from heartburn. Heartburn is usually due to stomach acid flows up into the esophagus. This causes pain and a burning sensation in the throat when the esophagus has no protective lining against acid. The most common causes of heartburn on travel, is quickly consumed meals, strong spices, for fatty foods or too much alcohol. The type of heartburn usually comes after meals.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - although the treatment of heartburn\r\n\r\n* Take antacid medication, available without prescription in many countries.\r\n* Do you have prescription medication at home, remember to bring it.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - heartburn and danger signals\r\n\r\nWhen heartburn, there are danger signals that should cause you to seek medical help.\r\n\r\n* Pain when you swallow.\r\n* Bloody vomiting.\r\n* Bloody or black stools.\r\n* Breathing difficulties.\r\n* Dizziness or pain that radiates into the neck and shoulder.', 'Heartburn', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'heartburn', '', '', '2012-06-18 10:20:38', '2012-06-18 10:20:38', '', 413, 'http://dlvs-uk.konscript.net/?page_id=1059', 0, 'page', '', 0),
