(1068, 2, '2012-01-12 10:16:54', '2012-01-12 10:16:54', 'Venereal diseases such as HIV, hepatitis B, gonorrhea, chlamydia and syphilis occur worldwide. The incidence is especially high among prostitutes. In some parts of the world, such as sub-Saharan Africa and Southeast Asia, the incidence of the deadly disease HIV and hepatitis B is very high.\r\n\r\nUsing a condom provides good protection against STDs, but the protection is not 100 percent. Although the journey is of longer duration and they fall in love with a new partner, use condoms until you are sure that the new partner is not carrying an STD.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - STDs:\r\n\r\n* Always use a condom.\r\n* Keep yourself to have condoms on the trip and check the expiration date.\r\n* Avoid having sex with prostitutes.', 'Sexually transmitted diseases', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'sexually-transmitted-diseases', '', '', '2012-06-18 10:20:38', '2012-06-18 10:20:38', '', 413, 'http://dlvs-uk.konscript.net/?page_id=1068', 0, 'page', '', 0),
