(1456, 1, '2012-01-13 09:11:37', '2012-01-13 09:11:37', 'The quality of the health system is fully compatible with the Danish in many countries. In some developing countries, the quality however much, and outside major cities is the opportunity for qualified medical care is often poor and transportation time for medical care can be long.\r\n\r\nIn many countries, for example. Sub-Saharan Africa and Southeast Asia, the risk of infection with chronic hepatitis (hepatitis B or C) and HIV / AIDS present at the treatment of disease. The infection can be transmitted by blood transfusions and through syringes, needles and other instruments that are reused.\r\n\r\nTravel advice - illness and treatment abroad:\r\n\r\n* Make no treatment with blood or blood products are not tested or cooked.\r\n* Make no injections with reused equipment. You must ensure that used sterile equipment.\r\n* Try to avoid dental visits.\r\n* Acupuncture treatment can involve a risk of infection.\r\n* Get not done tattoos.\r\n* Do not pierce.\r\n* Please bring disposable needles from home. Sold as travel kit at many pharmacies.\r\n* Read the section on travel insurance.', 'Treatment abroad', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1039-revision-7', '', '', '2012-01-13 09:11:37', '2012-01-13 09:11:37', '', 1039, 'http://flufighters.org.uk/1039-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1457, 1, '2012-04-30 07:36:38', '2012-04-30 07:36:38', '<div>\r\n\r\n<strong><img src="http://www.flufighters.org.uk/sites/default/files/dr-bill-holmes.jpg" alt="Dr Bill Holmes" width="120" height="146" align="right" hspace="10" vspace="10" />“</strong>We pride ourselves in delivering our vaccination programmes to the highest clinical standards. Our primary focus is the safety and comfort of those receiving the vaccine.\r\n\r\nThe flu vaccines that we use are the same as those provided by the NHS, manufactured under guidance from the World Health Organisation, and in 2012 will also protect against swine flu.\r\n\r\nOur customers receive the best possible service and highest levels of medical care. Our vaccinations are delivered by qualified nurses who have received training in flu vaccine delivery. Nurses conduct the onsite clinics with comprehensive medical kits.\r\n\r\nWe offer a 24-hour telephone medical support-line in case your employees have any queries regarding their vaccination.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions regarding our clinical processes and practices, please <a title="Email Dr Bill Holmes..." tabindex="24" href="mailto:drbillholmes@evguk.co.uk">contact me</a>.<strong>”</strong>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.flufighters.org.uk/sites/default/files/dr-bill-holmes-signature.jpg" alt="Dr Bill Holmes'' signature" width="100" height="33" />\r\n\r\nDr Bill Holmes F.R.C.P, F.R.C.G.P, D.Occ.Med\r\nMedical Director\r\n\r\nTo book call <strong>0845 521 0030 </strong>and let Flu Fighters help defend your organisation.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Clinical Excellence', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '325-revision-11', '', '', '2012-04-30 07:36:38', '2012-04-30 07:36:38', '', 325, 'http://flufighters.org.uk/325-revision-11/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
